pr_review_comment_body:
@benjaminp do you mean something like?
```
def ensure_binary(s, encoding='utf-8', errors='strict'):
    if isinstance(s, text_type):
        return s.encode(encoding, errors)
    elif isinstance(s, binary_type):
        return s
    else:
        raise TypeError("not expecting type '%s'" % type(s))
```
I'd like to keep the `raise TypeError` part to fail the error loudly; be consistent with the `raise` behavior from `ensure_string`.

I don't see any pros / cons at the moment to allowing the size 0 case of `ixmin == ixmax`.
So I'm merging this now.

@astrofrog and all - feel free to make follow-up PRs proposing changes to this check any time.

Perhaps something like this:
```
def pupilCoordsFromPoint(self, point):
    if hasattr(point, '__len__'):
        ra = [ p.ra for p in point ]
        dec = [ p.dec for p in point ]
        return self.pupilCoordsFromFloat(ra, dec)
    else:
        return self.pupilCoordsFromFloat(point.ra, point.dec)
```

When was this fixed?

I remember https://github.com/nteract/hydrogen/issues/597 and the [issue on `spawn-rx`](https://github.com/paulcbetts/spawn-rx/issues/11
) is still open

`def call_process(self, cmd):
     if not isinstance(cmd, list):
          exceptionhandler('Command is not a list.\n{0}'.format(str(cmd)))
     process = subprocess.Popen(cmd, stdout=subprocess.PIPE, stderr=subprocess.PIPE)
     out, err = process.communicate()
     if process.returncode != 0:
          exceptionhandler('Command execution failed.\n{0}\nError Message:{1}'.format(cmd, err)
     else:
          logging.info(out)`

I wrote this in the browser... so if there is any off syntax, ill catch it before commit.  This changes the flow a little.  It will either dump if the command execution failed and carry the command used and return the shell error in the log and output in the exceptionhandler, or it will log any output that may have come from the command.
